    },
    "aggreementC": {
      "title": "C. I will implement appropriate access security so as to ensure that only the authorized individuals mentioned in Section I of this Data Access Application Form be allowed to access the research data. This requires, for example, that if the consortium research data is stored on a shared computer system or on a file server, that it be password or encryption-protected. Moreover, if the computer(s) that hold the consortium research data are backed up, the backed up media must also be encrypted and stored in a secure location.",
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "aggreementD": {
      "title": "D. I understand that anyone who will use the consortium’s research data (mentioned in Section I of this Data Access Application Form) should be trained in the responsible use of participant information and be familiar with the terms and conditions of the Data Access Agreement. I am responsible for transmitting and familiarizing the other research personnel and students with the restrictions on access and use of the consortium research data. They must also be briefed on the security plans described in this section.",
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "aggreementE": {
      "title": "E. I understand that if the consortium research data is stored on a network-accessible computer, there should be measures in place to prevent access by computer hackers or contamination by viruses and spyware.",
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "aggreementF": {
      "title": "F. I understand that upon completion of my research project, I must destroy all local copies, including backups of the data accessed from the consortium. However, if necessary, I can still keep the consortium research data for archival purposes in conformity with national audits, publication or legal requirements. I must also either store my analysis code or send a copy of it to the consortium in case of potential needs to reproduce my variables or findings at a later date.",
